<P>
   EXCLUSIVE-AGENCY-CORRUPTION _ The front-line role of the Customs
Service in the government's war against illegal drugs has left the
agency highly vulnerable to narcotics-related corruption, Customs
officials acknowledged Tuesday in a report to Congress. By David
Johnston.
</P>
<P>
   GORE-POLITICS _ Vice President Al Gore has emerged from the
impeachment ordeal in a more commanding position to capture the
Democratic nomination than he would have if the world had never
heard of Monica Lewinsky. Most significantly, Dick Gephardt has
decided not to take on Gore. And among Republicans there is such a
feeling of inevitability to the vice president's quest to succeed
Clinton that former Vice President Dan Quayle, in announcing his
exploratory committee last week, proclaimed: ``I will win the
nomination. And I will beat Al Gore.'' By Richard L. Berke.
</P>
