<P>
   AIRFARE-DISCOUNTS (Undated) _ With international business travel
weakening because of the economic slowdown overseas and with more
flights scheduled across the North Atlantic, several major airlines
have aggressively cut their fares to Europe, exceeding in many
cases their previous winter sales. By Edwin McDowell.
</P>
<P>
   WEIGHT-WATCHERS (New York) _ Just two years ago it was a dud.
But Weight Watchers, while still a small part of H.J. Heinz, the
Pittsburgh-based company, is now the fastest-growing division in
Heinz's empire of Star-kist canned tuna, Smart Ones and Budget
Gourmet frozen dinners, Nine Lives pet food, baby food, pickles and
ketchup. By Constance L. Hays.
</P>
