<P>
   &UR; SOME ANSWERS TO THE KURDISH QUESTION &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Commentary) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By The Editorial Board of The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Kurdish PKK party, which organized the mass takeover of
Greek embassies around Europe Tuesday, is a hard outfit. No one
should be in any doubt about that. Nor should there be any doubt
about the party's leader, Abdullah Ocalan, whose rapid ejection
from the Greek embassy in Nairobi and extradition to Turkey has set
off this explosion of protest.
</P>
<P>
   Ocalan is a terrorist with an appalling record of murder and
torture.
</P>
<P>
   But, like the IRA, the PKK is a mirror image of the forces that
have suppressed it. These are peoples for whom history has shown no
remorse... &QL;
</P>
