<HEADLINE>
SUN DEVILS GAIN DEPTH ON LINE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Arizona State added more depth to its offensive line with the
signing of Steve York, a 6-foot-5, 300-pound junior college
transfer from Forney, Texas.
</P>
<P>
   York is attending junior college in Oklahoma and will have three
years of eligibility.
</P>
<P>
   He is the sixth offensive lineman and 11th junior college player
to commit to ASU.
</P>
<P>
   York was a three-year starter at Forney High School. During his
senior season, the Jackrabbits went 9-3 and two of their running
backs each gained more than 1,000 yards. Several recruiting
publications listed York as one of the top 100 seniors in the
country.
</P>
<P>
   He gave Washington an oral commitment in 1997 but had a change
of heart and signed with Baylor. He redshirted his first season and
then transferred to a Mississippi junior college, where he played
football this past season before transferring to a junior college
closer to home.
</P>
<P>
   Four of the Sun Devils' six offensive line recruits are 6-5 or
taller, and all weigh in at 300 pounds or more.
</P>
<P>
   Twenty-eight players have signed letters of intent, and ASU may
add another soon. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
