<P>
   AUSCHWICZ-LASTDAYS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ In the Auschwitz
death camp and for the following 50 years, Irene Zis-blatt kept
silent about the horrors she saw and lived through. Persuaded
finally to tell her story to the Survivors of the Shoah Visual
History Foundation, the nonprofit organization founded by filmmaker
Steven Spielberg, Zisblatt discovered a new wave of liberation. And
now, Zisblatt's story is a key part of the Oscar-nominated
documentary feature, The Last Days. The film concentrates on the
end of World War II, when Germany realized defeat was inevitable,
but continued exterminating the Jews. (Erstein, Palm Beach Post)
WITH PHOTOS. MOVED.
</P>
