<P>
   SCI-SLOW-LIGHT (Undated) _ A Danish physicist working at Harvard
has been able to slow the speed of light down to the pace of a fast
walk by shining it through a strange quantum state of matter called
a Bose-Einstein condensate. Besides being good for demonstrating
all kinds of fun relativistic effects, this breakthrough may lead
to the development of radically new optical devices in
communication and computing that can work at extremely low light
levels. By Malcolm W. Browne. (800 words)
</P>
