   DOW-REUTERS (New York) _ Dow Jones and Reuters form a link to
offer their news wires on Reuters screens.
</P>
<P>
   HOLOCAUST-HISTORIANS (Undated) For the banks, insurers and other
companies named in them, the mounting wave of Holocaust-related
lawsuits has created a litigation and public-relations nightmare.
But the lawsuits have also created a mini-boom for one unlikely
group: historians and research specialists. Corporations ranging
from Ford to General Motors to Bertelsmann have hired well-known
academics to write their wartime histories or scour ancient file
rooms worldwide for damaging or exculpatory information. At stake
are hundreds of millions of dollars in settlements, potential
public embarrassment, and even business complications. And often
the race is simply for companies to find disquieting information
before their adversaries do. By Barry Meier.
</P>
