<HEADER>
A8728 &Cx1f; tab-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SPIRITUALITY-VALUES-A     02-17 0342
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPIRITUALITY-VALUES-ADVISORY-NYTSF </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   EDITORS:
</P>
<P>
   DIANA BUTLER BASS is considered one of the finest
spirituality/lifestyle writers in the country. Her columns are
available from the New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
<P>
   Two of her recent pieces are summarized below. To purchase them
as ``separate buy'' articles please contact syndicate sales
representative DEBRA WEYDERT at 732-390-4480).
</P>
<P>
   TINKY WINKY GETS ALL THE INK, BUT `DIPSY' REFLECTS A DEEPER
ISSUE
</P>
<P>
   Teletubbyland, which we've all been reading about lately, is an
inclusive and pluralistic place. The Rev. Jerry Falwell failed to
mention that Dipsy, one of Tinky Winky's friends, is a Teletubby of
color. As the Teletubbies love and accept Tinky Winky without
reference to his orientation (and questionable taste in handbags),
they also love and accept Dipsy without reference to his darker
skin.
</P>
<P>
   But for many children, loving and accepting Dipsy may be a more
difficult and important task than determining Tinky Winky's
ambiguous sexuality. (Slugged TELETUBBY-THEOLOGY. 850 words)
</P>
<P>
   MID-LIFE SPIRITUALITY SHUNS `QUESTION-AND-ANSWER' RELIGION
</P>
<P>
   The spirituality of growing up and being grown-up is not the
same. Youthful spirituality seeks answers for big questions: Who is
God? Who am I? Who will be my life partner? What am I to do in the
world? A quest for order engulfs the young as they become
independent persons. As a result, religions with strict moral
boundaries and clear-cut beliefs appeal to teen-agers and young
adults, providing direction to those otherwise adrift.
</P>
<P>
   By forty, spirituality is no longer about order. Rather, it is
about meaning. For most of us, those ``big questions'' have been
resolved. As the last baby-boomers turn forty, an entire generation
is moving away from question-and-answer religion to narrative faith
-- a shift likely to produce profound consequences for America's
religious institutions and political landscape. (Slugged
ADULT-SPIRITUALITY 850 words.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
