UNDATED: 1/2 inch thick. 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Cooking:
</P>
<P>
   4 tablespoons peanut or corn oil
</P>
<P>
   Place wide frying pan over medium heat until hot. Add 2
tablespoons oil, swirling to coat sides. Add half of coins and
cook, turning once, until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes on each
side. Repeat with remaining oil and coins.
</P>
<P>
   Place on serving platter and serve hot.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 103 calories, 4 grams fat, 12
grams carbohydrates, 4 grams protein, 10 milligrams cholesterol,
106 milligrams sodium, 36 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   STEAMED FISH WITH SIZZLING LEMON GRASS OIL
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4-6
</P>
<P>
   3 dried black mushrooms
</P>
<P>
   2 stalks lemon grass (bottom 6 inches only)
</P>
<P>
   4 green onions
</P>
<P>
   Soak mushrooms in warm water to cover until softened, about 20
minutes; drain. Discard stems and halve caps. Cut each piece of
lemon grass into 3 slanting slices. Julienne 2 green onions; leave
2 green onions whole.
</P>
<P>
   Sizzling lemon grass oil:
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons cooking oil
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons sesame oil
</P>
<P>
   1 stalk lemon grass (bottom 6 inches only), thinly sliced
</P>
<P>
   Combine oils with lemon grass in saucepan.
</P>
<P>
   Fish dressing:
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup soy sauce
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons chicken broth
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon oyster-flavored sauce
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons sugar
</P>
<P>
   Combine soy sauce, broth, oyster-flavored sauce and sugar in
another saucepan.
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 to 2-pound whole fish, such as sea bass or red snapper,
cleaned
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon white pepper
</P>
<P>
   10 slices ginger, each the size of a quarter, lightly crushed
</P>
<P>
   On each side of fish, cut 3 diagonal slices, 3/4 inch deep,
across body. Sprinkle fish inside and out with salt and pepper.
Place piece of mushroom, lemon grass and ginger in each slit. Place
whole green onions in center of heat-proof dish; lay fish on top.
</P>
<P>
   Prepare a wok for steaming. Cover and steam fish over high heat
until fish turns opaque, 8 to 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Sprinkle half the julienned green onions over fish. Heat pans of
lemon grass oil and fish dressing until hot. Drizzle oil over fish,
then pour dressing over. Garnish with remaining julienned green
onions.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 216 calories, 10 grams fat, 6
grams carbohydrates, 24 grams protein, 42 milligrams cholesterol,
952 milligrams sodium, 42 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   BRAISED TOFU AND MUSHROOMS
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4-6
</P>
<P>
   14-ounce package extra-firm tofu, drained
</P>
<P>
   Cut tofu in half horizontally to make 2 pieces, each about 3/4
inch thick, With 2-inch biscuit cutter, cut 6 rounds from each half
to make a total of 12 rounds.
</P>
<P>
   Sauce:
</P>
<P>
   2/3 cup vegetable broth
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons black bean garlic sauce
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons oyster-flavored sauce
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon sesame oil
</P>
<P>
   Combine sauce ingredients in a bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Cooking:
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons cooking oil
</P>
<P>
   1 leek (1 inch in diameter), white part only, cut into
1/4-inch-thick rounds
</P>
<P>
   1/2 pound small white button mushrooms
</P>
<P>
   1/4 pound oyster mushrooms
</P>
<P>
   6 medium fresh shiitake mushrooms, stems discarded
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoons cornstarch dissolved in 1 tablespoon water
</P>
<P>
   Place nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat until hot. Add 1
tablespoon oil, swirling to coat sides. Add tofu and cook, turning
once, until golden brown, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on each side. Remove
pan from heat.
</P>
<P>
   Place wok over high heat until hot. Add remaining 1 tablespoon
oil, swirling to coat sides. Add leek and all mushrooms; stir-fry
for 1 minute. Add sauce, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until
mushrooms are tender, about 5 minutes. Add cornstarch solution and
cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens.
</P>
<P>
   To serve, arrange tofu in circle around edge of serving plate.
Place mushroom mixture in center.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 191 calories, 12 grams fat, 11
grams carbohydrates, 12 grams protein, trace cholesterol, 296
milligrams sodium, 58 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
