</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BABY'S-BEST-FRIEND-ADVISORY-NYTSF </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Noticed all the baby strollers in your neighborhood?
</P>
<P>
   You're witnessing an echo of the Baby Boom. Those babies and
their parents, your readers, need advice and support _ and they can
get it every week from  &UR; Dr. T. Berry Brazelton, America's most
respected pediatrician and longtime columnist for The New York
Times Syndicate. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Brazelton is an American institution: Professor Emeritus at
Harvard, which recently named a chair in his honor. Best-selling
author of more than two dozen books on child-rearing. Tireless
champion of children and families.
</P>
<P>
   In his weekly column ``Families Today,'' Dr. Brazelton guides
readers through a child's development, from teething to the
terrible twos and beyond, in essays and Q&AMP;As _ A MAGNET FOR YOUR
LIFESTYLE SECTION.
</P>
