 ART ADV.: Photos with URBAN-LABOR, VENTURE-INTERNET and
RETIREMENT-CAMPUS are being transmitted to NYT Photo Service
subscribers.  
 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-TINKY (London) _ When the Rev. Jerry Falwell outed one
of the Teletubbies, Britons responded with guffaws. By Kevin
Cullen. 615 words. (i and e coding)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-IMMIGRATE (Paris) _ Europe has an ulterior motive for
solving the Kosovo crisis: Fleeing ethnic Albanians are overrunning
immigration quotas, something only peace can halt. By Kevin Cullen.
1270 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
