Rabbit; for the Vietnamese, the Year of the Cat. For all concerned,
it's a season of eating, gift-giving and symbolism. Houses are
cleaned to rid them of bad fortune. New clothes in bright colors
(particularly red) are readied. Homes are stocked with food and
flowers. ``No matter where you are,'' says Chinese master chef
Martin Yan, ``you try to go home for the new year.'' And one of the
main reasons for going home again is to get some of the dishes that
foster good fortune and prosperity. By BEVERLY BUNDY. Story will
