<P>
   &UR; DAVID-LETTERMAN LATE SHOW TOP TEN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Signs the President is Trying to Kill You'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   10. He goes on TV to assure the nation that he's not trying to
kill you.
</P>
<P>
   9. You get a card from Saddam reading ``Glad I'm not you.''
</P>
<P>
   8. You turn on CNN and see your house in green night-vision.
</P>
<P>
   7. You wake up next to the head of Donna Shalala.
</P>
<P>
   6. You overhear him arguing with lawyers over legal definition
of the word ``strangle.''
</P>
<P>
   5. Keeps promising to ``introduce you to Vince Foster''
</P>
<P>
   4. He asks U.N. to pass resolution authorizing use of force
against you.
</P>
<P>
   3. Now under construction in Arlington Cemetery: ``The Tomb of
the Unknown Guy the
</P>
<P>
   President's Going to Kill''
</P>
<P>
   2. ``Someone'' throws a Big Mac stuffed with a brick through
your window.
</P>
<P>
   1. Two words: exploding cigars
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BILL'S WORLD &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By Bill Tammeus, The Kansas City Star &LR;
</P>
<P>
   More than 100 persons have been nominated for this year's Nobel
Peace Prize. Oh, great. Something else for people to fight over.
</P>
<P>
   On their trip to Mexico, Bill and Hillary Clinton spent nearly
three hours having dinner with the country's president and his
wife, who no doubt were careful not to serve peach mints.
</P>
<P>
   Mexico is the second largest market for U.S. exports, behind
only Canada. Bet some of what the Mexicans buy is stuff to sell to
American tourists so they'll feel at home.
</P>
<P>
   For Valentine's Day, Mr. Clinton gave his wife a gold
heart-shaped pin. No word on what she gave him. Maybe her own vote
for acquittal?
</P>
<P>
   Al Gore called the impeachment trial votes ``a reaffirmation of
the wisdom of our founders.'' This guy could have been president.
Why is he so happy?
</P>
<P>
   Now that the impeachment trial is over, Republicans seem to be
working to make sure people don't think GOP stands for Get Our
President.
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Clinton says he's ``profoundly sorry'' for what he said and
did that led to the impeachment trial. That may have been the only
pro part to this whole amateurish affair.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton scandal note: If, a year from now, you can still
identify Andrew Bleiler, Lucianne Goldberg and William Ginsburg,
you need to get a life.
</P>
<P>
   Hillary Rodham Clinton is deciding whether to run for the Senate
from New York. The state, apparently, is now some kind of Arkansas
suburb.
</P>
<P>
   Whatever was causing all those American Airlines pilots to be
ill must have been contagious. It quickly made passengers both sick
and tired.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
