<P>
   IMMIGRATION _ WASHINGTON _ Immigration and Naturalization
Service Commissioner Doris Meissner holds a 1:45 p.m. EST briefing
to announce that the agency's fiscal 1999 budget funds more than
1,600 positions for new Border Patrol agents and other kobs. She
also addresses additional resources for the INS detention program,
which has come under criticism from Congress members.(Schultz, Cox
News Service).
</P>
