   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ Microsoft never suggested in a 1995
meeting with Netscape officials that ``a line be drawn'' to
illegally divide the Internet browser market, a Microsoft executive
said Tuesday. Released testimony by Daniel Rosen in the federal
antitrust trial contradicted a potentially damaging assertion made
earlier by Netscape's chief executive officer, James Barksdale.
(Glass, Cox News Service).
</P>
