<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ Microsoft never suggested in a 1995
meeting with Netscape officials that ``a line be drawn'' to
illegally divide the Internet browser market, a Microsoft executive
said Tuesday. Released testimony by Daniel Rosen in the federal
antitrust trial contradicted a potentially damaging assertion made
earlier by Netscape's chief executive officer, James Barksdale.
(Glass, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   SCANA-NCUTILITY _ Scana Corp. says its $900 million acquisition
of Public Service of North Carolina, a gas utility that serves the
Research Triangle area, will more than double its cusotmer base and
bring ``critical mass'' to its Georgia gas retail business, where
it's the leading marketer. (Quinn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   GA-JOB-BIAS _ Women and minorities in Georgia face more
on-the-job discrimination than workers in any other Southern state,
according to a Rutgers study released in Atlanta. The study details
the nature and extent of discrimination by industry, region and job
categories, using EEOC data filed by companies with more than 50
workers. Georgia also ranked in the bottom 25 percent of the nation
in its treatment of women and minorities, the report added.
(Joyner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BLACK-BUYPOWER _ ATLANTA _ Black buying power survey may be
released today by Ken Smikle at Target Market News. (Poole, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SKI _ ATLANTA _In an era when even barber shops are regulated,
the Legislature left one business completely free of regulation _
ski resorts. A bill in the House would change that by forbiding
bouncing on lifts and require skiers to maintain control of their
descent down. (Kempner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HARBINGER _ Harbinger Corp is expected to announce new
technology and an update since the sweeping changes of October.
Co-founder C. Tycho Howle, called back from semiretirement to run
the company again, has a conference call this morning with
analysts. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BIZMAGS _ With billions of dollars flowing into index funds,
stock market research available on the Internet and thousands of
individuals turning to on-line trading, who needs a stock broker?
asks Business Week in a profile of the investor revolution brought
on by the computer and the Internet. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   DELL _ Dell shares fall in very heavy trading at midday.
(Mahoney, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   MOTOROLA _Motorola Inc. Wednesday has entered a manufacturing
alliance with Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co., in which TSMC
will make a wide range of chips for Motorola. This is Motorola's
biggest move toward its goal of outsourcing more of its
manufacturing. (Gallaga, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-SLOGAN _ Texas Department of Economic Development unveils
its new state state tourism campaign - and it's a lot like the old
one. The slogan, in fact, is the same: Texas - It's like a Whole
Other Country. (Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
