are moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-CHIPPER-DIVORCE _ Braves third baseman Chipper Jones and his
wife are heading for divorce court. (CRogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-NOTES _ Braves notebook. (CRogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15-18.
</P>
<P>
   REDS_BELINDA _ Stan Belinda used to worry about giving up home
runs. It was the worst thing in the world. Then the Cincinnati Reds
pitcher was diagnosed with multiple sclerosis. Now he's continuing
his baseball career on medication and he takes the game in stride.
(McCoy, Dayton Daily News). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-BELLSOUTH _ The BellSouth is preparing for field with a
distinct European flavor because of its new date on the weekend
before the Masters. (Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13-15.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-ITEMS _ Odds and ends package. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18-20.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-NOTES _ National golf notebook. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
