reform, Madison Democrat Rep. Tammy Baldwin was the only House
members chosen to speak at a White House event Wednesday. Hurt
</P>
<P>
   WYOMING -- MARRIAGE. Wyoming's federal lawmakers said Wednesday
they want to repeal the so-called ``marriage penalty,'' a tax that
forces married couples to pay an average of $1,400 a year more in
federal taxes than unwed people living together. Davant
</P>
