</P>
<P>
   _ Home appliances. Most home electronic products will not be
affected by the Y2K bug. However, FEMA recommends that people check
with manufactures to make sure any appliances they consider
essential are Y2K-compliant.
</P>
<P>
   Copies of the FEMA guide can be ordered by calling
1-800-480-2520 or by logging on to the agency's Web site at
www.fema.gov/y2k.
</P>
</TEXT>
