<HEADLINE>
GORDON N. CONVERSE, 78; AWARD-WINNING PHOTOJOURNALIST 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By TOM LONG  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Gordon Noble Converse of Needham, Mass., retired chief
photographer and photo editor of the Christian Science Monitor,
died Sunday in Newton-Wellesley Hospital. He was 78.
</P>
<P>
   As a photographer for the Monitor for more than 40 years, Mr.
Converse traveled to more than 120 countries and visited some of
them several times. He won more than 50 awards from the Boston
Press Photographers Association and twice received the Brotherhood
Award of the National Conference of Christians and Jews.
</P>
<P>
   He was born in Stoneham, Mass. He attended Tilton Junior College
and served in the Navy during World War II.
</P>
<P>
   He leaves his wife, Shirley (Wixon); two daughters, Linda Bloom
of Greenwich, Conn., and Deborah Foti of Wayland, Mass.; and six
grandchildren.
</P>
<P>
   A memorial service will be held at 11 a.m. Saturday in Bigelow
Chapel at Mount Auburn Cemetery in Cambridge, Mass.
</P>
