   PROSECUTOR-DRUGS (Seattle) _ Will Miller, a former prosecutor
who put felons away in Seattle and New York, now faces five felony
drug charges and the possibility of 10 years in prison.
</P>
<P>
   By Scott Sunde. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-TULIPS (Undated) _ Tulips entice with their vibrant
colors, their sensuous shape, their delicate grace, their promise
of summer to follow. It is difficult to imagine that they could
create fortunes, prompt bankruptcies, undermine heads of state,
spur intrigues, engender passions, foster art in various mediums
and enflame unquenchable obsessions. Yet this is indeed the amazing
history of the tulip, as British gardening writer Anna Pavord makes
clear in her ``The Tulip: The Story of a Flower tThat Has Made Men
Mad.''
</P>
<P>
   By John Marshall. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SONICS (Seattle) _ Seattle SuperSonics host Sacramento.
</P>
<P>
