 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-CIR-KIDS-WEB-NYT, which moved in
``a'' news file.) 
c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``In some ways it's as if companies are entering our homes and
picking the brains of our children for commercial purposes.''
</P>
<P>
   _KATHRYN MONTGOMERY, president of the Center for Media
Education, on advertising on the Web aimed at children.
</P>
