<HEADER>
A9399 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-FALCONSBENNETT-CU     02-17 0365
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-FALCONSBENNETT-CUT18-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Falcons release veteran Bennett
 &HT;    By Matt Winkeljohn
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The Atlanta Falcons terminated the contracts of
weakside linebacker Cornelius Bennett and center/guard Dave Widell
on Wednesday in a cost-cutting measure that paves the way for
former Georgia Tech standout Keith Brooking to become a starter in
his second season.
</P>
<P>
   The final season of Bennett's four-year, $13.6 million contract
called for a salary of $2.4 million. Widell, who dressed for just
two games last season, was due $500,000, and running back Harold
Green, who was released last Friday, was due $550,000.
</P>
<P>
   Counting bonuses the Falcons would have likely owed Bennett and
Green, the combined $3.775 million the team saves leaves Atlanta
roughly $7 million under next season's NFL salary cap.
</P>
<P>
   That's room enough for Atlanta to set its sights higher in a
fast-dwindling free agency market. The team lacks a cornerback and
a strong safety.
</P>
<P>
   Bennett, who played the first nine seasons of his 12-year career
for Buffalo, led Atlanta with 121 total tackles, breaking middle
linebacker Jessie Tuggle's nine-year reign.
</P>
<P>
   But Tuggle ($3.85 million) and Bennett ($3.7 million) would have
carried the second- and third-highest salary-cap charges on the
team next season behind quarterback Chris Chandler's $4.7 million.
</P>
<P>
   The two linebackers, who will be 34, would have made up 13
percent of the team payroll.
</P>
<P>
   Plus, coach Dan Reeves said Brooking (cap charge: $1.32 million)
needs to play. Brooking had 22 of his 30 total tackles, his
interception, and his sack in the final eight regular-season games.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's a position we can get somebody (else) in there and give
us some cap room,'' Reeves said. ``We've got a No. 1 draft choice
(Brooking) we think can play, and we've got to get him on the
field.
</P>
<P>
   ``Cornelius proved he can still play well, and this also gives
him a chance to see what his market value is.''
</P>
<P>
   The Falcons will carry cap charges next season of $1.25 million
for Bennett, $200,000 for Green and $50,000 for Widell.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
