<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRANSAMERICA-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 Transamerica Trading Fuels Takeover Talk  &HT;       
 By Arthur M. Louis 
 &HT;     c. 1999 San Francisco Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
Heavy activity yesterday in the stock and options of Transamerica
Corp. revived rumors that the San Francisco financial-services
company could be on the verge of a merger or takeover.
</P>
<P>
   On a day when the stock market in general declined steeply,
Transamerica shot up $1.81 to $57.63 on the New York Stock
Exchange, reaching its highest level in more than a month. At one
point yesterday, the stock sold as high as $59.88
</P>
<P>
   Transamerica officials did not respond to a request for comment.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts have been saying for more than a year that Transamerica
eventually might merge with another company.
</P>
<P>
   There have been massive consolidations lately in the
financial-services industry _ most notably between Travelers and
Citicorp, forming Citigroup _ and Transamerica, with about $6
billion in annual revenues, generally is considered too small to
stand alone.
</P>
<P>
   ``We live in a time of consolidation,'' Colin Devine, an analyst
with Salomon Smith Barney, told Reuters. ``It's fair to say that
when you look at potential consolidation candidates, Transamerica
is among the top on the list.''
</P>
<P>
   More than a million Transamerica shares changed hands yesterday,
the first time that has happened in more than six months.
</P>
<P>
   On the Philadelphia Stock Exchange, where Transamerica options
are traded, activity was extraordinarily heavy in the company's
call options, each of which gives buyers the right to buy 100
shares of the company's stock at a fixed price before a fixed date.
</P>
<P>
   A total of 1,374 February call options _ allowing purchasers the
right to buy the stock through Friday's session _ changed hands
yesterday. In addition, investors bought 444 March call options _
allowing investors to buy the stock through March 19.
</P>
<P>
   By contrast, the total volume for Transamerica's February put
options _ giving investors the right to sell the stock _ amounted
to just 20 contracts yesterday. Sales of March put options totaled
16 contracts.
</P>
<P>
   Options traders said the prices of Transamerica call options
sold yesterday were substantially higher than normal, based on
standard valuation measures.
</P>
<P>
   The March options were trading at levels suggesting that the
buyers think there's a strong chance that the stock will move up as
much as 60 percent in the coming year.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
COL. 1 of TRANSAM1 (37030 ) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   END OF STORY  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
