A9435 &Cx1f; taf-z
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-AFGHAN-TERRORIST-NYT &LR;      02-17 0308
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AFGHAN-TERRORIST-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TALIBAN SAYS BIN LADEN IS GONE 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 By PHILIP SHENON   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ A top official of the Taliban, the armed religious
group that controls most of Afghanistan, said Wednesday that Osama
bin Laden, the world's most-wanted terrorist suspect, is no longer
in Taliban territory.
</P>
<P>
   ``We do not know where he is,'' said the official, Abdul Hakeem
Mujahid, a Taliban diplomat assigned to the United Nations who met
Wednesday with senior U.S. officials. ``He decided himself to
leave. He is not in the area of control of the Taliban.''
</P>
<P>
   An anti-Taliban alliance in Afghanistan said on Tuesday that its
troops had sighted bin Laden in Afghanistan in recent days.
</P>
<P>
   State Department officials said they had no evidence to support
the Taliban claim about bin Laden, who has been indicted in the
United States in the bombing of two U.S. embassies in Africa last
August.
</P>
<P>
   But U.S. officials said they were heartened by the willingness
of the Taliban, which had long harbored bin Laden, to distance
itself publicly from the Saudi multimillionaire.
</P>
<P>
   Mujahid spoke with reporters here Wednesday after meeting with
Karl Inderfurth, the assistant secretary of state for South Asian
affairs. Inderfurth met in Pakistan this month with other Taliban
officials to demand that bin Laden be expelled from Afghanistan and
brought to justice.
</P>
<P>
   While the United States does not recognize the Taliban as the
government of Afghanistan, it maintains contact with it.
</P>
<P>
   Taliban leaders are eager to gain diplomatic recognition from
the United States, and to avoid a repetition of last summer's
American missile attack on an Afghan base camp used in the past by
bin Laden. That eagerness has given the Clinton administration
leverage in pushing for his expulsion from Afghanistan.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
