Once a ``poor boy from Queens,'' the novelist Robin Cook bought his
Louisburg Square town house in Boston after writing the best-seller
``Coma.'' Thirty years ago, the 27 town houses that line the square
sold for about $100,000, but recent sales in the carefully
preserved area have exceeded $4 million. (Evan Richman/New York
Times Photo)
