<SLUG> BC-RENEGADE-RAPPER-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WU-TANG CLAN RAPPER ARRESTED IN L.A. FOR WEARING FORBIDDEN BODY
ARMOR
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY GREG GITTRICH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- One month after New York City police arrested
rapper Ol' Dirty Bastard for shooting at two officers during a
traffic stop, Los Angeles police had their own run-in with the
performer Tuesday night in Hollywood.
</P>
<P>
   Police didn't have to dodge any bullets this time, but the
rapper -- whose real name is Russell Jones -- was ready for a
violent confrontation.
</P>
<P>
   Jones was arrested for wearing a bullet-resistant vest inside
his car, police said. He was charged with possessing body armor and
released after posting $18,000 in bail. The charges could carry a
prison sentence of 16 months to three years.
</P>
<P>
   Federal law prohibits the 29-year-old entertainer and convicted
violent felon, who also goes by the stage name Big Baby Jesus, from
owning or wearing any type of body armor, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Police pulled over the Wu-Tang Clan rap group member at 10:45
p.m. Tuesday for driving erratically on Whitley and Yucca avenues,
one block north of Hollywood Boulevard.
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday night's arrest was the latest incident involving the
controversial rapper during the past year.
</P>
<P>
   In September, Jones was arrested and accused of threatening to
kill his ex-girlfriend in Los Angeles. Two months later, he was
arrested after police said he threatened security guards at a blues
club in the city.
</P>
<P>
   The New York City shootout occurred Jan. 15 when police pulled
Jones over for driving with his headlights off in Brooklyn. Police
arrested Jones and a passenger following a car chase, but
detectives failed to recover a gun and a grand jury cleared Jones
of attempted murder charges. Jones insisted he never fired at
police, saying the officers were scared by his cellular phone.
</P>
<P>
   Jones, who has survived two shootings, gained notoriety last
year when he rushed the stage of the Grammy Awards at Radio City
Music Hall in New York City. Seizing the microphone, he complained
about losing in the best rap album category.
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
