<P>
   KOSOVO (Kostrce, Serbia) _ If the Kosovo Liberation Army's
negotiators are talking in France about peace, its officers in the
forbidding, frozen hills of southern Kosovo are still preparing for
war. ``No peace is possible without a military _ to live without a
military is not a serious idea,'' said Maj. Sadik Halitjaha. ``No
one here trusts the Serbs, with their brutal expansionism and their
megalomania. No one can trust them after they burned our villages,
poisoned our wells, killed women and children and cut out the eyes
of the dead.'' By Steven Erlanger.
