<P>
   SUICIDE-REPORT (Salem, Ore.) _ In the first year under the
nation's only assisted-suicide law, 15 terminally ill people in
Oregon used it to end their lives, and there was no evidence they
suffered painful, lingering deaths as opponents had warned. By Sam
Howe Verhovek.
